gomodel:SYNGO_3040  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Title: \"Actinfilin Is a Cul3 Substrate Adaptor, Linking GluR6 Kainate Receptor Subunits to the Ubiquitin-Proteasome Pathway\"\n\nNote: Cul3; Cullin-3 is a \"scaffold for the Cul3-based E3 ubiquitin-ligase complex (30-32).\"\n\nFig.6: \"Cul3 regulates GluR6 expression in vivo\"\n\nFig.7: \"Actinfilin and Cul3 negatively regulate surface expression of GluR6\"\n- \"We found that decreasing actinfilin levels via RNAi significantly increased surface GluR6 expression in dendritic spines, as assessed morphologically and by increased co-localization with PSD-95 (Fig. 7, A-D and H) and synaptophysin (Fig. 7H). Synaptic GluR6 more than doubled (Fig. 7H), and the size of the GluR6-containing puncta increased 1.8-fold (mean punctal area ± S.E.: control neurons, 0.12 ± 0.01 μm2; RNAi-AF expressing neurons, 0.22 ± 0.01 μm2). \". Experimental description: - \" Hippocampal neurons were cultured from E18 rats...\"\n- \"The complete rat actinfilin cDNA and truncations were subcloned into the pGADT7 prey...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3040" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

